HEADWORD: Waybung
<hw>Way"bung`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>An Australian insessorial bird (<spn>Corcorax melanorhamphus</spn>)
noted for the curious actions of the male during the breeding season. It
is black with a white patch on each wing.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Wayed</ent>⟦br⟧
